---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Ezri" description="A cosmos for your inner world. Reflection without optimization.">
  <div class="hero">
    <h1>Ezri</h1>
    <p class="tagline">A cosmos for your inner world.</p>
    <span class="badge mt-md">In Development</span>
  </div>

  <section class="container">
    <p class="lead">
      Ezri is a space for reflection — not optimization.<br />
      A mirror, not a map.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>What It Is</h2>
    <p>
      A reflective inner-development engine. A protected cosmos where humans
      learn to see themselves — and each other — clearly, ethically, and
      without domination.
    </p>
    <ul class="features">
      <li>A private space to explore what's inside — without performance or judgment</li>
      <li>Archetypes, patterns, shadows — met at your pace, on your terms</li>
      <li>Other perspectives offered gently — no comparison, no competition</li>
      <li>Room to grow — not toward a destination, but into yourself</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>What It Is Not</h2>
    <p>
      Ezri is <strong>not</strong> a productivity tool, mental health app,
      social network, belief system, or spiritual authority.
    </p>
    <p>
      It does not promise healing, enlightenment, or certainty.
    </p>
    <p>
      It offers clarity, reflection, and ethical space.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>The Principle</h2>
    <blockquote>
      The system reflects. It does not direct.
    </blockquote>
    <p>
      Ezri never interferes with your autonomy, pace, or identity formation.
      No optimization toward "success." No nudging toward beliefs. No gamified
      attention extraction.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container note-section">
    <h2>A Note on Inner Work</h2>
    <p>
      Reflection can surface things that are tender, confusing, or difficult.
      This is part of the process — but it's not something to face alone.
    </p>
    <p>
      If at any point you feel overwhelmed, please pause.
      <a href="/resources" class="text-link">Here are some places to find support</a>.
    </p>
    <p class="privacy-note">
      Your inner world belongs to you. Ezri is designed so your data stays private,
      unanalyzed, and never sold.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container text-center">
    <p class="text-muted">
      More soon.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .lead {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    text-align: center;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .features {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .features li {
    padding: var(--space-sm) 0;
    padding-left: var(--space-md);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--accent-subtle);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  blockquote {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent-warm);
    padding-left: var(--space-md);
    margin: var(--space-md) 0;
  }

  .note-section {
    background: var(--bg-elevated);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .note-section h2 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .note-section p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .text-link {
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .text-link:hover {
    color: var(--accent-glow);
  }

  .privacy-note {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
</style>
